news.summary: Activision (ATVI) disclosed that it received a request for information from the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission and a grand jury subpoena from the Justice Dept

news.headline: Microsoft releases patch for RCP vulnerability (why you need to act quickly)
news.summary: While the RCP vulnerability may seem simple to patch and mitigate on the surface, historically, many organizations have struggled to deploy critical security patches until it''s too late.

news.headline: Microsoft reportedly wants to bring ads to free-to-play Xbox games
news.summary: Microsoft is reportedly developing an advertising program for "select" companies to insert non-disruptive ads into free-to-play games.

news.headline: Activision cooperating with federal insider trading probes -filing
news.summary: Activision Blizzard is cooperating with federal investigations into trading by friends of its chief executive shortly before the gaming company disclosed its sale to Microsoft Corp, it said in a securities filing on Friday. It received requests for information from the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission and received a subpoena from a Department of Justice […]

news.headline: Activision Says It Will Cooperate With Insider Trading Investigations
news.summary: The company received requests for information that appeared to relate to investigations into whether investors who knew Bobby Kotick, Activision’s chief executive, traded Activision stock a deal with Microsoft was made public.

news.headline: Microsoft Xbox Games to Insert Ads In-Game? New Venture Might be Coming Soon
news.summary: Microsoft is teasing new in-game ads for Xbox, and the titles will see ads in the middle, like YouTube videos or Spotify ads.

news.summary: A new program might allow developers to make even more money off their games.

news.headline: Microsoft May Soon Allow Ads in Free-to-Play Xbox Games
